						 <p>This was a pretty good spin on an old cliche. Usually in these sorts of things, the Foundation grabs the idiot ball and is somehow absolutely unable to tell they’re being played. Here, they can tell, but it simply doesn’t matter, which is where the horror comes from. The Foundation’s own learned traits of experimentation and study work against it here.</p> <p>+1, all hail the Rounderpage.</p> 
